<item>
<title>We Reap What We Sow</title>
<itunes:title>We Reap What We Sow</itunes:title>
<itunes:author>Dan Doolittle</itunes:author>
<itunes:subtitle>
Guthrie Assembly Meeting 12/22/2023
</itunes:subtitle>
<itunes:summary>
<![CDATA[
Dan Doolittle delivers a sermon reflecting on lessons from King Solomon's life. It analyzes how even the wisest person failed to tend his 'vineyard' by neglecting humility and kindness over time, leading to conflict and division. 
Despite wisdom to counsel others, Solomon did not heed warnings and planted seeds of arrogance reaped in bitterness. 
Core themes cover the universal laws of sowing and reaping, need for self-reflection, seeking God's wisdom, and living with love and humility daily to bear good fruit.
]]>
</itunes:summary>
